aXcelerate, a leading SaaS provider that powers millions of learners' course
and competency records throughout Australia, has been recognized as a Great
Place to Work®. This recognition is based on employee feedback, and it means
that aXcelerate is a company where employees feel valued, respected, and
supported.

We’re looking for a Software Developer to join the Digital - Mobile Apps
subdivision to deliver high quality and secure software. As part of an agile
team, this role will be primarily responsible for all facets of the aXcelerate
Mobile App and in addition but not limited to projects of the LMS module.

** Our Brisbane-based office offers hybrid work options however we welcome applications from remote candidates within Australia. **

** Responsibilities: **

  * Develop and design robust, maintain, scalable applications, ensuring optimal performance and a seamless user experience. 
  * Modifying software to fix errors, upgrade interfaces and improve system performance 
  * Develop and/or maintain solution documentation including data and component models 
  * Ensure / maintain consistent functionality and user experience (feature parity) across different platforms (Android / iOS / Web) 
  * Write clean, well-documented code which adhere to aXcelerate development standards 
  * Perform/Request code reviews to maintain code quality across the team 
  * Utilise version control system (Git) to manage codebase changes and collaborate effectively with other developers 
  * Collaborate with cross-functional teams, contribute to technical discussions and decision-making 
  * Collaborate with UI/UX designers to implement new features 
  * Document and record estimated time and effort time required for project tasks and manage related work via JIRA tickets 
  * Stay up-to-date with best practices / trends / emerging technologies to contribute to the team’s technical growth 

** About you **

  * Experience with HTML / CSS / JavaScript / TypeScript 
  * Experience with React/React Native 
  * Experience with working with RESTFul APIs and handling asynchronous operations 
  * Experience with version control tools such as GIT 
  * Passionate about all things software and development 
  * Adaptability/Flexibility - Willingness to learn new technologies and adapt to evolving development practices 
  * Ability to effectively prioritise and execute tasks accordingly 
  * Ability to work both independently and in a team-oriented, collaborative environment 

** What’s on offer **

  * A vibrant, supportive and team-oriented culture, with regular team activities and social events 
  * A focus on professional development, with internal and external training and a personal $2000 professional development budget each year. 
  * Access for you and your family to an Employee Assistance Program and resources 
  * Opportunities for career advancement, we nurture our talent and provide career pathways across the business. 
  * On-site healthy snacks, coffee machine, regular breakfasts and celebrations. 
  * Hybrid working environment, office close to public transport 

** **

** Our interview process: **

  * Meet with one our recruitment team 
  * Complete a Technical Assessment 
  * Interview with the Hiring Team 

